s of global warming and resource depletion, The Constant Fire shows us how to move beyond this stale debate into a more profound experience of the world as sacred—a world that embraces science without renouncing human spirituality.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aBible and sciencexHistory. 0aReligion and sciencexHistory. 7aSCIENCE / General.2bisacsh  aastrophysics.  abig bang.  aclimate change.  acontroversial debate.  acultural debate.  aeinstein.  aethos.  aevolution.  aflood myths.  agiordano bruno.  aglobal warming.  ahuman spiritual existence.  ahuman spirituality.  ahumanity.  aireland.  amicroscopes.  amodern world.  amultiverse.  amythology.  amythos.  aneolithic archaeological site.  aphilosophy.  apolitical debate.  areligion.  areligious experience.  aresource depletion.  asacred narratives.  asacred pursuits.  ascience and religion.  ascience.  ascientists.  aspiritual.  aspirituality.  astar formation.  atelescopes.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052025412140uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052094203540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520942035423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520942035/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY